#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:69
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "&kappname; is a fun and exciting game for &kde; desktop environment. "
#| "&kappname; is modeled after the well known pen and paper based game of "
#| "Dots and Boxes."
msgid ""
"&ksquares; is a fun and exciting game. &ksquares; is modeled after the well "
"known pen and paper based game of Dots and Boxes."
msgstr ""
"O &kappname; é un xogo divertido e emocionante para o entorno de escritorio "
"&kde;. O &kappname; baséase no famoso xogo de papel e bolígrafo dos Cadrados."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:70
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "The idea behind &kappname; is to construct squares by interconnecting the "
#| "dots on the grid. Up to four players can play this game together, taking "
#| "turns. The trick is – regardless of who has constructed most of the "
#| "square, it is the player who completes the square that gets the point for "
#| "it."
msgid ""
"The idea behind &ksquares; is to construct squares by interconnecting the "
"dots on the grid. Up to four players can play this game together, taking "
"turns. The trick is – regardless of who has constructed most of the square, "
"it is the player who completes the square that gets the point for it."
msgstr ""
"A idea do &kappname; é construír cadrados conectando os puntos da "
"cuadrícula. Poden xogar ata catro xogadores, cada un na súa quenda. O truco "
"consiste en que non importa quen construíse a maior parte dun cadrado, é o "
"xogador que completa o cadrado o que obtén un punto por el."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:71
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To win the game round player has to collect the most points by covering the "
"most area with the squares of player's own color."
msgstr ""
"Para gañar unha partida hai que obter o maior número de puntos cubrindo a "
"maior área posíbel cos cadrados da cor de cada un."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:74
#, no-c-format
msgid "How to Play"
msgstr "Como xogar"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:76
#, no-c-format
msgid "Objective:"
msgstr "Obxectivo:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:76
#, no-c-format
msgid "Complete more squares than any of your opponents."
msgstr "Completar máis cadrados que o resto dos adversarios."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:78
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"At the start of the game, the game board is empty. There is simply a grid of "
"dots showing where lines can be drawn."
msgstr ""
"No inicio do xogo o taboleiro está baleiro. Simplemente hai unha grade con "
"puntos que amosan onde se poden debuxar as liñas."

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:88
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "Game Board"
msgid "&ksquares; Game Board"
msgstr "Taboleiro de xogo"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:93
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each player takes it in turns to draw a line between two adjacent dots on "
"the board. By hovering the mouse over the game board, a yellow indicator "
"line will show you where your line will be placed when you click. Once you "
"have decided where you want to draw your line, click - and the line will be "
"drawn. If by drawing a line, you completed a square then this square now "
"belongs to you and earns you a point. Each time you complete a square, you "
"must draw another line. If your line did not complete a square then the next "
"player(s) take their turn. The game will continue until every square on the "
"board is owned by one of the players."
msgstr ""
"Cada xogador debuxa unha liña entre dous puntos contiguos. Ao pasar o rato "
"por riba do taboleiro, unha liña indicadora en amarelo mostra onde "
"aparecería unha liña ao premer - preme e debúxase esa liña. Se ao debuxares "
"unha liña completas un cadrado, ese cadrado perténcelle e gañas un punto. "
"Cada vez que completes un cadrado tes que debuxar outra liña. Se a liña que "
"debuxes non completa un cadrado, é a volta do xogador seguinte. O xogo "
"continúa ata que todos os cadrados do taboleiro teñan dono."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:98
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "To start a new game with custom settings (number of players, player "
#| "names, board size) click on the <guibutton>New</guibutton> toolbar button "
#| "or go to <menuchoice><shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;"
#| "<keycap>N</keycap></keycombo></shortcut><guimenu>Game</"
#| "guimenu><guimenuitem>New</guimenuitem></menuchoice>. To start a new game "
#| "with the same settings as the current game, click on <guibutton>Restart "
#| "Game</guibutton> on the toolbar."
msgid ""
"To start a new game with custom settings (number of players, player names, "
"board size) click on the <guibutton>New</guibutton> toolbar button or go to "
"<menuchoice><shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>N</keycap></"
"keycombo></shortcut> <guimenu>Game</guimenu> <guimenuitem>New</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice> menu item. To start a new game with the same settings as the "
"current game, click on <guibutton>Restart Game</guibutton> button on the "
"toolbar."
msgstr ""
"Para iniciar unha partida nova con opcións personalizadas (número de "
"xogadores, os seus nomes, o tamaño do taboleiro), preme o botón "
"<guibutton>Nova</guibutton> da barra de ferramentas ou vai a "
"<menuchoice><shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>N</keycap></"
"keycombo></shortcut><guimenu>Partida</guimenu><guimenuitem>Nova</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice>. Para iniciar unha partida coas mesmas opcións que "
"na que estás, preme <guibutton>Reiniciar a partida</guibutton> na barra de "
"ferramentas."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:103
#, no-c-format
msgid "Game Rules, Strategies and Tips"
msgstr "Regras do xogo, estratexias e suxestións"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:106
#, no-c-format
msgid "Game Rules"
msgstr "Regras do xogo"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:107
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "There is very little to be said when it come to the rules, as the game "
#| "concept in itself is rather a simple one. Nevertheless, here are the game "
#| "regulations you, as a player will defiantly face while playing &kappname;:"
msgid ""
"There is very little to be said when it come to the rules, as the game "
"concept in itself is rather a simple one. Nevertheless, here are the game "
"regulations you, as a player will defiantly face while playing &ksquares;:"
msgstr ""
"Pouco hai que dicir no que fai ás regras, dado que o concepto do xogo é "
"bastante sinxelo en si mesmo. Porén, velaquí as regras do xogo ás que te has "
"de enfrontar cando xogues ao &kappname;:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:109
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You may only connect the dots on the grid if they are not previously "
"connected by you, your opponent, or the computer."
msgstr ""
"Só podes conectar os puntos da grade se non conectáchedes antes ti, o teu "
"adversario ou o computador."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:110
#, no-c-format
msgid "To gain the points you have to connect the dots to form a square."
msgstr ""
"Para gañar os puntos hai que conectar os puntos para formar un cadrado."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:111
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The square can be no larger than the four adjacent dots on the grid allow "
"for."
msgstr ""
"O cadrado non pode ser maior que o que permiten os catro puntos adxacentes "
"da grade."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:112
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Once a square is complete the player who draws the last line of that square "
"is granted the right of possession over it. The square then is colored and "
"the player is given a point."
msgstr ""
"Unha vez completado un cadrado, o xogador que debuxase a última liña dese "
"cadrado recibe a súa posesión. O cadrado recibe a cor do xogador e este "
"recibe un punto."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:113
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The player who completes the square is given an extra turn which the player "
"cannot forfeit."
msgstr ""
"O xogador que completa o cadrado recibe unha volta extra que non pode saltar."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:117
#, no-c-format
msgid "Strategies and Tips"
msgstr "Estratexias e suxestións"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:119
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Try not to play at random. Such game practice will most certainly result in "
"loss."
msgstr ""
"Intenta non xogar ao chou. Este tipo de xogo seguro que remata cunha perda."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:120
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Construct long chains of lines over the gameboard. Once one such chain is "
"complete start to build another one going parallel to the first."
msgstr ""
"Constrúe cadeas longas de liñas no taboleiro. Unha vez que unha desas cadeas "
"estea completa, comeza a construír outra que vaia paralela á primeira."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:121
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Try not to build contraptions where only one line remains undone. Your "
"opponent will almost certainly take an advantage of it."
msgstr ""
"Intenta non construír tarecos nos que só quede unha liña desfeita. O teu "
"opoñente aproveitarao con casi total seguridade."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:122
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you are to let the opponent get a square or more, try to select the "
"combination resulting in the least damage."
msgstr ""
"Se tes que permitir que o teu adversario constrúa un cadrado ou máis, "
"intenta escoller a combinación que produza o menor dano posíbel."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:123
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Try to push your opponent into the situation where he/she(it) will have no "
"choice but to let you get the square."
msgstr ""
"Intenta empurrar o teu adversario a unha situación na que non teña máis "
"remedio que deixarche coller o cadrado."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:124
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you are to get a chance to start completing a whole chain of squares, "
"remember that by leaving two squares at the end of such chain incomplete you "
"are pushing your opponent into completing them, thus giving you the "
"opportunity to continue onto yet another chain. Such a situation is called "
"the double-cross."
msgstr ""
"Se tes a posibilidade de comezar a completar unha cadea completa de "
"cadrados, lembra ao que deixares dous cadrados do final desa cadea "
"incompletos, estás empurrando o teu adversario a completalos, dándoche así a "
"oportunidade de continuares noutra cadea. Esta situación chámase a cruz "
"dobre."

